        <h3>Budget-Friendly Centerpiece Options</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Themed centerpieces with team memorabilia</li>
          <li>Photo collage centerpieces (action shots from the season)</li>
          <li>Custom 3D printed sports centerpieces (reusable for multiple events)</li>
          <li>Team-colored flowers and decorations</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Creating the Program & Agenda</h2>
        <p>Most successful sports banquets run 2 to 2.5 hours. A typical structure: 30 minutes for social time, 45-60 minutes for dinner, 5-10 minutes for a season highlight slideshow, 30-45 minutes for awards and speeches, and 10-15 minutes for closing remarks.</p>

        <h2>10 Award Categories Every Banquet Needs</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Most Valuable Player (MVP)</strong> — The standout performer</li>
          <li><strong>Most Improved Player</strong> — Recognizes growth and dedication</li>
          <li><strong>Coach's Award</strong> — Heart of the team, leadership beyond stats</li>
          <li><strong>Offensive Player of the Year</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Defensive Player of the Year</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Rookie of the Year</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Sportsmanship Award</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Teammate of the Year</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Academic All-Conference</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Four-Year Letterman Recognition</strong></li>
        </ul>

        <p><a href="/award-ceremony/">Read the full Award Ceremony Guide →</a> for detailed tips on presenting each award.</p>

        <h2>Photography & Memory-Making</h2>
        <p>Designate someone to take photos throughout the event. A simple photo station with a team-branded backdrop lets families capture the moment. Consider setting up a tripod with a remote clicker for group shots.</p>

